    h3 Minor UX Improvements
    p There are a few additional user interface improvements that could be made in order to make the experience more enjoyable for users.
    p With so much content to read through, it’s helpful to provide users with some sort of progress indicator that represents how far they’ve already scrolled and how much more content they have to get through. Visual progress indications gamify the experience for the user and incentivize the consumption of content.
    img(src="images/csdt-8.png" style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px")
    p Most of my participants became confused at one point or another when they forgot which page they were on and were unable to immediately see their current location. By simply highlighting the user’s current page in the left navigation menu, this issue can be easily avoided.
    img(src="images/csdt-9.png")
    p Lastly, to help users navigate the content within each page, it would be helpful to add one more layer of sub-pages to the left navigation menu.
    img(src="images/csdt-10.png" style="max-width: 50%; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px")
    h2 Conclusion
    p I really enjoyed the opportunity to combine my user experience design and research abilities with the material from this class. While building out these changes is an entirely different beast, I hope that the research data and recommendations I’ve presented here provide a decent starting point for future work on the African Fractals portion of the CSDT site.